---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does it cost to clear a blocked drain in Pakenham?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A straightforward blocked drain in Pakenham or Cardinia typically clears for $180-$450 with a machine or hydro-jet. A CCTV drain camera inspection to find and prove the cause is usually $250-$400 and is often credited against the clearing work. Worked example: a Cardinia Lakes home with tree roots in the sewer at the back boundary usually pays around $450-$650 for a hydro-jet clear plus a CCTV inspection that confirms exactly where the roots enter, so we can quote a no-dig reline if the pipe is cracked." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why do tree roots keep blocking my drain in Cardinia Lakes?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The early-2000s estates &mdash; Cardinia Lakes, Lakeside, Heritage Springs &mdash; were planted with fast-growing street and garden trees that are now 15-20 years old. Roots are drawn to the moisture and nutrients in the sewer and find the smallest gap at a clay-pipe joint, then grow into a mat that traps grease, wipes and paper. Cutting the roots clears it for now; if the joint or pipe is damaged, a no-dig reline stops them coming back." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you fix a blocked drain without digging up my yard?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Often, yes. We first CCTV the line to see the exact problem. If it is roots or a build-up, a hydro-jet clears it. If the pipe is cracked or has root-intruded joints, we can usually pipe-reline &mdash; a resin liner is cured inside the existing pipe to create a new seamless pipe within it &mdash; so there is no excavation, no destroyed lawn or driveway, and the joints roots used to enter are sealed." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What can I do to stop drains blocking?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Keep wipes (even 'flushable' ones), fats, oils and food scraps out of the system, fit drain strainers in showers and the kitchen, and if you have mature trees over the sewer line consider a periodic preventative hydro-jet. We can CCTV your main line once to map root-entry points so you know which sections to keep an eye on &mdash; useful in the older Cardinia Lakes, Lakeside and Heritage Springs estates." }
    }
  ]
};
---
<Layout
  title="Blocked Drains Pakenham | CCTV, Hydro-Jet, Root Cutting | (03) 9003 0108"
  canonical="https://pakenhamplumbers.com.au/services/blocked-drains/"
  description="Blocked drain plumber for Pakenham, Officer, Cardinia Lakes &amp; Cardinia Shire. CCTV drain camera, hydro-jet clearing, root cutting and no-dig pipe relining for tree-root, grease &amp; collapsed-pipe blockages. From $180.">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">CCTV &middot; hydro-jet &middot; no-dig reline</span>
      <h1>Blocked drains in <span class="accent">Pakenham &amp; Officer</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Slow sink, gurgling toilet, sewage smell or water backing up? We find the exact
        cause with a CCTV drain camera, clear it with a hydro-jet, cut tree roots and,
        where the pipe is damaged, reline it without digging up your yard.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>How we clear a blocked drain.</h2>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">

        <h3>1. CCTV drain camera &mdash; find the real cause.</h3>
        <p>
          We push a waterproof camera down the line to see exactly what is blocking it
          and where. Roots at a joint, a grease and wipe build-up, a sagging belly in the
          pipe, or a cracked or collapsed section all look different and need different
          fixes. A camera inspection is usually $250&ndash;$400 and is often credited
          against the clearing work.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">2. Hydro-jet &amp; root cutting &mdash; clear it.</h3>
        <p>
          A hydro-jet uses high-pressure water to scour the pipe wall clean &mdash; far
          more thorough than an old electric eel. For tree roots we use a cutting head to
          slice the root mat out and flush it away. A straightforward clear is
          <strong>$180&ndash;$450</strong>.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">3. No-dig pipe relining &mdash; stop it coming back.</h3>
        <p>
          If the CCTV shows cracked pipe or root-intruded joints, clearing alone is a
          temporary fix &mdash; the roots return. A relining job cures a resin liner inside
          the existing pipe, creating a smooth new pipe within it and sealing the joints
          roots used to enter. No excavation, no destroyed lawn or driveway.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Why drains block in Cardinia&rsquo;s estates.</h3>
        <p>
          The early-2000s <strong>Cardinia Lakes, Lakeside and Heritage Springs</strong>
          estates were planted with fast-growing trees that are now 15&ndash;20 years old.
          Their roots have reached the clay-bedded sewer and stormwater lines and find the
          smallest joint gap, then mat up and trap grease and wipes. This is the first big
          wave of root-intrusion blockages on the corridor &mdash; it is our most common
          call-out in the established estates.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Worked example.</h3>
        <p>
          A Cardinia Lakes home with tree roots in the sewer near the back boundary
          usually pays around <strong>$450&ndash;$650</strong> for a hydro-jet clear plus
          a CCTV inspection that confirms exactly where the roots enter, so we can quote a
          no-dig reline if the pipe is cracked. Where we connect to or alter the sanitary
          drain we work to <strong>AS/NZS 3500</strong> and meet South East Water
          requirements, with a Certificate of Compliance where the work is prescribed.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Drains we clear.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Sewer lines &mdash; toilets, showers, gully traps backing up</li>
          <li>Kitchen and laundry waste &mdash; grease and food build-up</li>
          <li>Stormwater and downpipe lines &mdash; leaf and silt blockages</li>
          <li>Collapsed and root-intruded clay pipe in the older estates</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Where we work.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-lakes/">Cardinia Lakes</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/lakeside/">Lakeside</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/heritage-springs/">Heritage Springs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/officer/">Officer</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/beaconsfield/">Beaconsfield</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-shire/">All Cardinia Shire</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Drain blocked in Pakenham?</h2>
        <p>CCTV diagnosis, hydro-jet clear, no-dig reline. Sewage backing up? Call now &mdash; that&rsquo;s a <a href="/services/emergency-plumber/" style="color:#fff;text-decoration:underline;">24/7 emergency</a>.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
